---
layout: base.njk
title: Home
---

<div id="root">
	<header class="heading-container">
		<a href="/">
			<h1 class="heading">A Believable Fiction</h1>
		</a>
	</header>

	<main class="article-list">
		<article class="article-excerpt">
			<header class="heading">
				<h2>About...</h2>
			</header>
			<section class="article-section-text">
				<p>
					A Believable fiction is a rather ambitious, and attempting
					to be eloquent blog written by a somewhat fictional
					character in an attempt to make sense of a strange world
					that the character inhabits.
				</p>
				<p>
					In all seriousness there is no specific rhyme or reason to
					any post on the page, anything fanciful or mundane might be
					written, edited, and just as well removed as needed, but at
					least something will be there.
				</p>
			</section>
		</article>
		<article class="article-excerpt">
			<header class="heading">
				<h2>...Me</h2>
			</header>
			<section class="article-section-text">
				I am an India based software developer specializing in web
				technologies amongst several other things. I have a great love
				of stories and songs, drama and DnD, Games and Theatery and
				above all people and their experiences
			</section>
		</article>
		<article class="article-excerpt">
			<header class="heading">
				<h2>Posts</h2>
			</header>
			<ul class="list-of-links">
				{% for post in collections.post %}
				{% if not post | isDraft %}
				<li>
					<a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a>
				</li>
				{% endif %}
				{% endfor %}
			</ul>
		</article>

		<article class="article-excerpt">
			<header class="heading">
				<h2>Lists</h2>
			</header>
			<section class="article-section-text">
				Some collections of mundane, and less than mundane for glancing
				at later, or a record of what could've been something greater
			</section>
			<ul class="list-of-links">
				{% for list in collections.list %}
				<li>
					<a href="{{ list.url }}">{{ list.data.title }}</a>
				</li>
				{% endfor %}
			</ul>
		</article>

		<article class="article-excerpt">
			<header class="heading">
				<h2>Weeknotes</h2>
			</header>
			<section class="article-section-text">
				Some people think structured outputs are really helpful, while I
				am scarce on belief on people, and even scarcer on belief in
				procedure the power of the scientific approach compels me
				otherwise. Is there wisdom to their words? Let us attempt to
				discover as we start using weeknotes.
			</section>
			<ul class="list-of-links weeknotes-list">
				{% for weeknote in collections.weeknotes.reverse() %}
				<li>
					<a href="{{ weeknote.url }}">{{ weeknote.data.title }}</a>
				</li>
				{% endfor %}
			</ul>
		</article>
	</main>
</div>
